NOTT ATWATER COMPANY, Appellant, v. Burns POE, Collector of Internal Revenue, etc., Appellee. No. 6231. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 17, 1930. Otto B. Rupp, of Seattle, Wash., and Alex M. Winston, of Spokane, Wash., for appellant. Anthony Savage, U. S. Atty., of Seattle, Wash., and John R. Wheeler, Sp. Atty., Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for appellee.

Before DIETRICH and WILBUR, Circuit Judges, and WEBSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Ordered judgment of District Court [33 F.(2d) 1000] affirmed; mandate forthwith,
